Citation.sAbstract: The surface tension of (2-methyl-2-butanol + ethanol), (3-methyl-1-butanol + ethanol), and (2-methyl-1-butanol + ethanol) binary solutions was measured over the entire composition range and at temperatures from (293.15 to 323.15) K. The experimental data were correlated with the temperature, the maximum deviation being less than 0.4 %.
Citation.sTitle: Surface Tensions of Three Amyl Alcohol + Ethanol Binary Mixtures from (293.15 to 323.15) K
